
ex_cep_tio_nal

exceptional = 非常好的 / 特別出色的

1. 直接修飾 (放在名詞前)
Exceptional service (卓越的服務)
The hotel provides exceptional service to every guest.
Exceptional results (優異的結果)
We achieved exceptional results this quarter.

2. 間接修飾 (放在 be 動詞後)
The quality is exceptional. (品質非常出色。)





the service was exceptional.
the performance was exceptional
the leadership skills were exceptional
the problem-solving abilities were exceptional
the talent was exceptional

小提醒
exceptional ≠ perfect
是「非常好」，但不一定 100 分
